1 cup Cheese Curds
8 tbsp Hummus
2 unit(s) Flatbread
1 unit(s) Carrot
6 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
2 unit(s) Honey
1 unit(s) Gala Apple

Cut each flatbread into 8 equal wedges.
Peel, then halve carrot crosswise, then cut into 1/2-inch matchsticks.
Core, then cut each apple into 8 equal wedges.

Wrap flatbread wedges in paper towels, then microwave on high for 1 min. (NOTE: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the flatbread!)

Plate carrot sticks and flatbread wedges with hummus and tzatziki alongside for dipping.
Serve cheese curds and apples on the side.
Drizzle honey over apple wedges.